OL,3,CChannel Islands see record-breaking
OL,4,Ctemperatures in May
OL,6,FJersey and Guernsey have experienced
OL,7,Ftheir hottest May and warmest Spring
OL,8,Fon record.
OL,10,FLast month, temperatures exceeded 30C
OL,11,Ffor five days in a row - something
OL,12,Fthat has never happened since records
OL,13,Fbegan in 1894.
OL,15,FTemperatures peaked at 34.2C on
OL,16,FTuesday 26 May - smashing the previous
OL,17,Fwarmest May day by roughly five
OL,18,Fdegrees.
OL,26,@rD@eOXwD@\OX
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1780423900
OL,3,CChannel Islands see record-breaking
OL,4,Ctemperatures in May
OL,6,FThis was the 11th hottest individual
OL,7,Fday on record and a higher than any
OL,8,Ftemperature recorded in June.
OL,10,F"I'm struggling to find a word to
OL,11,Fencapsulate quite how bizarre it is,"
OL,12,FRob Plummer said, forecaster at Jersey
OL,13,FMet.
OL,15,FHe added that temperature records are
OL,16,Fusually beaten by a fraction of a
OL,17,Fdegree, so to beat the record by five
OL,18,Fdegrees Celsius is highly unusual.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1780423900
OL,3,CChannel Islands see record-breaking
OL,4,Ctemperatures in May
OL,6,F"It doesn't mean that it will become a
OL,7,Fregular occurrence, and it doesn't
OL,8,Fnecessarily mean that the coming
OL,9,Fmonths will be even hotter," Rob said.
OL,11,FIn Guernsey, our average Spring
OL,12,Ftemperatures were 0.9C higher than
OL,13,Fthe previous record and 0.8C higher
OL,14,Fthan the last record in Jersey.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, the average temperature
OL,17,Facross May was 0.7C warmer than our
OL,18,Fprevious warmest May in both islands.
OL,26,@tD@VOXuD@\OXyD@SOX
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1780423900
OL,3,CChannel Islands see record-breaking
OL,4,Ctemperatures in May
OL,6,FThe warm weather put us into a
OL,7,Fheatwave - three consecutive days or
OL,8,Fmore where the daily maximum air
OL,9,Ftemperature reaches 28C.
OL,11,FMeteorologist Matthew Winter from
OL,12,FJersey Met told ITV News: "You can
OL,13,Fnever take one event on its own and
OL,14,Fcall that Climate Change.
OL,16,F"But this is certainly the sort of
OL,17,Fthing we'd expect to see under a
OL,18,Fwarming climate regime, for things to
OL,19,Fbecome hotter earlier in the year and
OL,20,Frecords to be broken more regularly."
OL,26,@qD@WOX
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/6
